    <h1>SSRI Toxicity & Serotonin Syndrome</h1>
    
    <div class="alert">
        <strong>Hunter Toxicity Criteria:</strong> Serotonin syndrome features a triad of altered mental status, autonomic instability (hyperthermia, tachycardia, diaphoresis), and neuromuscular hyperactivity (clonus, hyperreflexia - usually worse in lower extremities).
    </div>

    <h2>Weight-Based Resuscitation & Antidotes</h2>

    <div class="calc-box">
        <h3>1. Benzodiazepines</h3>
        <p>First-line therapy to control agitation, lower heart rate/blood pressure, and reduce muscle rigidity/hyperthermia.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Lorazepam:</strong> 0.05 - 0.1 mg/kg IV (Adult typical: 1-2 mg). Repeat every 10-20 min until sedated.</li>
            <li><strong>Diazepam:</strong> 0.1 - 0.2 mg/kg IV (Adult typical: 5-10 mg).</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="calc-box">
        <h3>2. Cyproheptadine</h3>
        <p>A specific 5-HT2A serotonin antagonist used for moderate to severe cases unresponsive to benzodiazepines.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Pediatric Dose:</strong> 0.25 mg/kg/day PO divided every 6 hours. (Max 12 mg/day).</li>
            <li><strong>Adult Dose:</strong> 12 mg PO initial loading dose. Then 2 mg PO every 2 hours until clinical response is seen. Maintenance is 8 mg every 6 hours.</li>
            <li><strong>Note:</strong> Only available orally. Can be crushed and given down an NG tube if the patient is intubated.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="calc-box">
        <h3>3. Supportive Care</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Hyperthermia:</strong> Active cooling. Avoid antipyretics (acetaminophen/ibuprofen) as the fever is caused by muscle activity, not hypothalamic set-point alteration. Paralysis/intubation may be required for temp > 41.1°C (106°F).</li>
            <li><strong>Restraints:</strong> Avoid physical restraints if possible, as pulling against them worsens severe muscle breakdown (rhabdomyolysis) and hyperthermia.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
